title: Stocks Close Week Higher, Q3 Reports In Full Swing
text: Next video starts in : 7 Play Stocks Close Week Higher, Q3 Reports In Full Swing  The most endangered presidential candidates  Unlock your personal NFL Now stream by signing in to NFL.com START by Investor's Business Daily Video 2:30 mins This week, stocks finished higher as earnings season is now in full swing. Two Fed policymakers indicated this week that the central bank should hold off on lifting interest rates this year amid disappointing economic data. The week's notable stock moves came from General Electric, Facebook, Wal-Mart and Netflix. Share this
